summary: This code imports the EfficientNetFilm model from the rtx package and instantiates an instance of it with the "efficientnet-b0" name and a target size of 10. The model is then used to process an image named "img.jpeg", and the result is stored in the variable out.

details.comment: This code imports the EfficientNetFilm model from the rtx package and instantiates an instance of it with the "efficientnet-b0" name and a target size of 10. The model is then used to process an image named "img.jpeg", and the result is stored in the variable out.
details.content:
from rtx.efficient_net import EfficientNetFilm
model = EfficientNetFilm("efficientnet-b0", 10)
out = model("img.jpeg")
